Definitely worth the $5. I use it to make movies for school, or just for fun. You can edit your frames in any way imaginable, plus there's a green screen feature so that you don't have to waste time on backgrounds. You can also turn down the green screen sensitivity, so that it doesn't block out everything. Plus you can add your own pictures, audio, and backgrounds, and save your movie to Google Drive or to downloads. If you're looking for the perfect studio, then stop looking. You found it.

This is the best stop motion app for mobile, no doubt about it. You can delete unused frames, copy and paste frames, use green/blue screen, add your own sound effects and music, add title cards, and (if you are willing to do a bit of fiddling) erase certain things out of individual frames, and that's not even scratching the surface of what you can do. This App looks like it is going to be the best of the bunch, it has the essential features you are going to need.  To this end it is very well thought trough by people who know what it ought to be able to do.  It feels intuitive to use and presents itself professionally without a childish interface or missing essentials.  However I have used it on a Hudl2 and Lenovo Yoga Tab 3 and suffered for it!  It exports unreliably, even when you export it as a stopmotionstudio project. So you can't clear stuff to archive and trust you have safely saved your work.  You end up having to import the work you exported to check it is not corrupted.  A very long drawn out process.  If you are selecting, cutting and pasting after you have inserted an audio clip or used paid features it can go bananas.  It will paste frames into odd places and the audio will often just not work, the corruptions can be irretrievable.  Every time you come out of a project it looses your exposure/white balance and focus settings which is a massive pain in the posterior as once you have your rig set up and your lighting sorted you need to be able to maintain continuity.  So much promise, such reliability issues.
